" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e4" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e8" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e5" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e5" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e8" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e6" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e6" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e6" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e6" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e8" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e7" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s2.e8" /></sentence><sentence text=" The use of conventional amphotericin B deoxycholate is limited by substantial toxicity that is either infusion-related or associated with renal failure"><entity charOffset="25-52" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s3.e0" text="amphotericin B deoxycholate" /></sentence><sentence text=" Its lipid derivatives, particularly liposomal amphotericin B (LAmB), are less nephrotoxic while maintaining a broad antifungal spectrum"><entity charOffset="47-61" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e0" text="amphotericin B" /><entity charOffset="63-67" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e1" text="LAmB" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s4.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" LAmB is active against most Candida spp"><entity charOffset="1-4" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s5.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=", including Candida glabrata and Candida parapsilosis, and against more resistant, emerging yeasts species such as Rhodotorula spp" /><sentence text=", Geotrichum spp" /><sentence text=" and Trichosporon spp" /><sentence text="" /><sentence text=" LAmB is also active against Cryptococcus spp"><entity charOffset="1-4" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s10.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" and all dimorphic fungi such as Histoplasma, Blastomyces, Coccidioidomyces, and Paracoccidiodomyces" /><sentence text=" The antifungal spectrum of LAmB is particularly interesting with regard to filamentous fungi, with marked activity against Aspergillus spp"><entity charOffset="28-31" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s12.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" and agents of zygomycosis" /><sentence text=" The latter might emerge during long-term treatment with voriconazole or an echinocandin, as these organisms are resistant to these drugs"><entity charOffset="57-69" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="76-88" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e1" text="echinocandin" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s14.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" We review here the role of LAmB in the current antifungal management strategy, which is based on results obtained in prospective trials"><entity charOffset="28-39" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s15.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" LAmB can be retained as first-line treatment for human immunodeficiency virus (HIV)-positive patients with disseminated histoplasmosis and cryptococcosis, even in the setting of renal impairment or concomitant administration of potentially nephrotoxic drugs"><entity charOffset="1-4" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s16.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" In addition, there is sufficient evidence that the drug should be a major consideration for the empirical treatment of persistent febrile neutropenia or as an alternative to for patients with invasive aspergillosis, for those at risk of renal impairment, major drug-drug interaction or liver insufficiency, particularly in the situation of an established azole intolerance"><entity charOffset="356-361" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s17.e0" text="azole" /></sentence><sentence text=" The primary licensed indication for LAmB is empirical treatment"><entity charOffset="37-41" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s18.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" When zygomycosis is suspected or has been documented, high doses of LAmB should be prescribed"><entity charOffset="69-72" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s19.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text=" Finally, LAmB may also be considered as a therapeutic option for the management of candidaemia and remains a cornerstone for the treatment of some visceral localisations during systemic candidosis"><entity charOffset="10-13" id="DDI-PubMed.18430132.s20.e0" text="LAmB" /></sentence><sentence text="" /></document>